@sectionX{Incompatibilities with Previous Versions}
@Addcontentsline{Incompatibilities with Previous Versions}

Lua 5.0 is a major release.
There are several incompatibilities with its previous version, Lua 4.0.

@subsectionX{Incompatibilities with @Index{version 4.0}}

@subsubsectionX{Changes in the Language}
@itemize{

@item{}
The whole tag-method scheme was replaced by metatables.

@item 
Function calls written between parentheses result in exactly one value.

@item 
A function call as the last expression in a list constructor
(like @T{{a,b,f()}}) has all its return values inserted in the list.

@item 
The precedence of @rwd{or} is smaller than the precedence of @rwd{and}.

@item 
@rwd{in}, @rwd{false}, and @rwd{true} are reserved words.

@item 
The old construction @T{for k,v in t}, where @T{t} is a table,
is deprecated (although it is still supported).
Use @T{for k,v in pairs(t)} instead.

@item 
When a literal string of the form @T{[[...]]} starts with a newline,
this newline is ignored.

@C{@item Old pre-compiled code is obsolete, and must be re-compiled.}

@item Upvalues in the form @T{%var} are obsolete;
use external local variables instead.

}


@subsubsectionX{Changes in the Libraries}
@itemize{

@item 
Most library functions now are defined inside tables.
There is a compatibility script (@T{compat.lua}) that
redefines most of them as global names.

@item 
In the math library, angles are expressed in radians.
With the compatibility script (@T{compat.lua}),
functions still work in degrees.

@item 
The @T{call} function is deprecated.
Use @T{f(unpack(tab))} instead of @T{call(f, tab)}
for unprotected calls,
or the new @T{pcall} function for protected calls.

@item 
@T{dofile} does not handle errors, but simply propagates them.

@item{}
@T{dostring} is deprecated. Use @T{loadstring} instead.

@item 
The @T{read} option @T{*w} is obsolete.

@item 
The @T{format} option @T{%n$} is obsolete.

}


@subsubsectionX{Changes in the API}
@itemize{

@item{}
@T{lua_open} does not have a stack size as its argument
(stacks are dynamic).

@item 
@T{lua_pushuserdata} is deprecated.
Use @T{lua_newuserdata} or @T{lua_pushlightuserdata} instead.

}



